### **2.2 Table Categories**

#### **A. USER MANAGEMENT (15+ tables)**
```sql
1. users
   - id, username, email, password, role
   - first_name, last_name, phone, avatar
   - email_verified_at, status, last_login_at
   - created_at, updated_at

2. user_roles
   - id, role_name, display_name, permissions_json
   - created_at, updated_at

3. user_profiles
   - id, user_id, bio, address, city, province
   - postal_code, country, date_of_birth, gender
   - company_name, company_position
   - created_at, updated_at

4. user_bank_accounts
   - id, user_id, bank_name, account_number
   - account_holder_name, branch, is_primary
   - created_at, updated_at

5. user_documents
   - id, user_id, document_type
   - (KTP, NPWP, Selfie, etc.)
   - file_path, verified_at, verified_by
   - created_at, updated_at

6. user_sessions
   - id, user_id, session_token, ip_address
   - user_agent, expires_at
   - created_at, updated_at

7. user_login_history
   - id, user_id, ip_address, user_agent
   - login_at, logout_at, status

8. user_notifications
   - id, user_id, title, message, type
   - is_read, read_at, link, icon
   - created_at

9. user_preferences
   - id, user_id, language (id/en)
   - timezone, currency, theme
   - email_notifications, push_notifications
   - created_at, updated_at

10. password_resets
    - id, email, token, expires_at, created_at

11. email_verifications
    - id, email, token, expires_at, verified_at

12. two_factor_auth
    - id, user_id, secret, backup_codes
    - enabled_at, created_at

13. user_kyc
    - id, user_id, kyc_level, verified_at
    - verified_by, notes
    - created_at, updated_at

14. user_addresses
    - id, user_id, label, address
    - city, province, postal_code
    - is_default, created_at, updated_at

15. user_activity_log
    - id, user_id, action, description
    - ip_address, user_agent
    - created_at
```

