## ğŸŒ **8. MULTI-LANGUAGE (ID & EN)**

### **8.1 Language Implementation**

```
Strategy: Manual translation (no auto-translate)
Languages: Indonesia (default) & English

Scope:
âœ… ALL public pages (homepage, services, pricing, etc.)
âœ… ALL dashboard pages (admin, client, partner)
âœ… ALL emails
âœ… ALL notifications
âœ… ALL error messages

Implementation:
- Language toggle di header (flag icon)
- Store preference in session/cookie
- Use translation files: /lang/id.php & /lang/en.php

Structure:
/lang/
  â”œâ”€â”€ id/
  â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ common.php
  â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ auth.php
  â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ dashboard.php
  â”‚   â””â”€â”€ errors.php
  â””â”€â”€ en/
      â”œâ”€â”€ common.php
      â”œâ”€â”€ auth.php
      â”œâ”€â”€ dashboard.php
      â””â”€â”€ errors.php
```

### **8.2 Translation Format**

```php
// Example: /lang/id/common.php
return [
    'welcome' => 'Selamat Datang',
    'login' => 'Masuk',
    'register' => 'Daftar',
    'logout' => 'Keluar',
    // ... more
];

// Example: /lang/en/common.php
return [
    'welcome' => 'Welcome',
    'login' => 'Login',
    'register' => 'Register',
    'logout' => 'Logout',
    // ... more
];

// Usage in views:
<?php echo lang('common.welcome'); ?>
// Output: "Selamat Datang" (ID) or "Welcome" (EN)
```

